    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="98"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)/11927: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-08T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 8, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Referring to my telegram No. 94, February 5, 11 a.m.<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d98fn14">Not printed.</note> I am in receipt of a letter<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d98fn15">Not found in Department files.</note> from the Minister of
                        Agriculture<note n="16" xml:id="d98fn16">Mariano R. Montealegre.</note>
                    stating that the President<note n="17" xml:id="d98fn17">Rafael Angel Calderón
                        Guardia.</note> is in principle in complete accord with the Memorandum of
                    Understanding. The Minister adds that his Ministry will take great pleasure in
                    cooperating in every way with the survey party which he trusts will come as soon
                    as possible.</p>
                <p>The Minister and I went over the Memorandum of Understanding this morning and he
                    suggested certain minor changes which I will submit by airgram for the
                    Department’s consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
